title: 820-2796 not start after liquid damage
message:
This MCP platform requires pressing power button to turn on.

Trigger SMC_ONOFF_L and check for pulse at PM_SLP_S4_L.
I supposed that SMC_ONOFF_L stays high normally.

Do you get C7755 correct voltage?

title: 820-2796 not start after liquid damage
message:
"i have remove U7500 and fan turn"
If you've turned on the board without U7500, you are really lucky if Q7560 didn't blow out.

Do NOT do this ever again.
Never ever let high-side MOSFET (in buck converter) with Gate pin "on air".
